  <thing id="sClrBodBir" name="Bodak Birth" description="The caster transforms one willing subject (which can be the caster) into a bodak.\nIgnore all of the subject&apos;s old characteristics, using the bodak description in the Monster Manual instead.\nBefore casting the spell, the caster must make a miniature figurine that represents the subject, then bathe it in the blood of at least three Small or larger animals.\nOnce the spell is cast, anyone that holds the figurine can attempt to mentally communicate and control the bodak, but the creature resists such control with a successful Will saving throw.\nIf the bodak fails, it must obey the holder of the figurine, but it gains a new saving throw every day to break the control.\nIf the figurine is destroyed, the bodak disintegrates.\n\n{b}Focus:{/b} Figurine of subject, bathed in animal blood.\n{b}Drug Component:{/b} Agony." compset="Spell" summary="Transforms a willing subject into a bodak.">
