  <thing id="gRedflower" name="Redflower Leaves" description="{b}Addiction:{/b} Low\n{b}Type/DC:{/b} Ingested 10\n{b}Price:{/b} 300 gp / (2-5 times the price where banned)\n{b}Alchemy DC:{/b} 27\n{b}Description:{/b}\n\nThese crushed leaves of a tiny red bog flower are known for their ability to improve hand-to-eye coordination.\n{b}Initial Effect:{/b} None.\n{b}Secondary Effect:{/b} As amove-equivalent action, the user may focus his attention upon a particular creature. If he follows that action with an attack against the creature, he gains a +4 competence bonus on the attack roll. This ability lasts 10 minutes.\n{b}Side Effects:{/b} None.\n{b}Overdose:{/b} Taking a second dose before the first has worn off causes the user to be nauseated for 1d4 &#215; 10 minutes.\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nTable 3&#150;4: Addictions\nAddiction Rating              Fort DC     Satiation                             Damage\nNegligible                                 4             1 day                  1d3&#150;2 Dex (can be 0)\nLow                                           6           10 days                1d3 Dex\nMedium                                  10             5 days                1d4 Dex, 1d4 Wis\nHigh                                         14             2 days                1d6 Dex, 1d6 Wis, 1d2 Con\nExtreme                                 25             1 day                   1d6 Dex, 1d6 Wis, 1d6 Con\nVicious                                   36             1 day                   1d8 Dex. 1d8 Wis, 1d6 Con, 1d6 Str\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------" compset="Gear">
