  <thing id="gSannish" name="Sannish" description="{b}Addiction:{/b} Medium\n{b}Type/DC:{/b} Ingested 9\n{b}Price:{/b} 15 gp / (2-5 times the price where banned)\n{b}Alchemy DC:{/b} 20\n{b}Description:{/b}\n\nA bluish liquid distilled from wolves&#146; milk and a powdered desert plant, this concoction is very popular.  Addicts are easily found by the permanent blue stains on their lips.\n{b}Initial Effect:{/b} 1 point ofWisdom damage.\n{b}Secondary Effect:{/b} The user becomes numbed to pain for 1d4 hours, immune to pain-induced penalties (such as from a symbol of pain).\n{b}Side Effects:{/b} Sannish causes euphoria. While the drug is in effect, the user takes a &#150;2 penalty on all initiative checks.\n{b}Overdose:{/b} A second dose taken while the first dose is still in effect causes a numbing stupor for 2d4 hours. The user can only take partial actions until the stupor wears off.\n\n{b}Homebrew Note:{/b} Sometimes used by healers in extremely small doses to numb pain.\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nTable 3&#150;4: Addictions\nAddiction Rating              Fort DC     Satiation                             Damage\nNegligible                                 4             1 day                  1d3&#150;2 Dex (can be 0)\nLow                                           6           10 days                1d3 Dex\nMedium                                  10             5 days                1d4 Dex, 1d4 Wis\nHigh                                         14             2 days                1d6 Dex, 1d6 Wis, 1d2 Con\nExtreme                                 25             1 day                   1d6 Dex, 1d6 Wis, 1d6 Con\nVicious                                   36             1 day                   1d8 Dex. 1d8 Wis, 1d6 Con, 1d6 Str\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------" compset="Gear">
