  <thing id="sDemGrCurs" name="Bestow Greater Curse" description="The caster places a curse upon the creature touched, choosing one of the following three effects.\n        (1) A single ability score is reduced to 1;  or two abilities take -6 penalty \n        (2) &#150;8 on attack rolls, saves, and checks; \n        (3) Each round the subject has a 25% chance to act normally, otherwise he takes no action.\n\nA player may invent a new curse, but it should be no more powerful than those listed above, and requires DM approval.\n\nA {i}greater curse{/i} cannot be dispelled. It can be removed with a {i}break enchantment{/i}, {i}limited wish{/i}, or {i}remove curse{/i}, but the caster attempting to break it must suceed on a caster level check (DC 15 + caster level of the creature who bestowed the curse). A {i}miracle{/i} or {i}wish{/i} automatically breaks the curse.\n\nWhen the spell is cast, the bestower can specify a single deed, event, or task that will remove the curse. The deed must be something accomplishable within one year, assuming the target undertakes the task immediately. The curse victim can have others help him with the task, and in some cases other characters may be able to accomplish the task and lift the curse for him." compset="Spell">
