  <thing id="cDiaVileDi" name="Vile Diabolism" description="An 8th-level diabolist can use her diabolism power to deal half the normal amount of extra unholy damage as vile damage (see Chapter 2 for an explanation of vile damage). For example, a fireball cast by a 6th-level wizard/8th-level diabolist deals 10d6 points of fire damage and 2d6 points of unholy damage. If the diabolist then rolls a 7 for the 2d6 points of unholy damage, she can (if she chooses) convert the unholy damage into 3 points of vile damage instead." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Can choose to sacrifice half their Diabolism damage to deal as Vile instead of unholy.">
