  <thing id="cLidLifewe" name="Lifewell" description="A lifedrinker stores the life energy that it steals in a reservoir in itself called a lifewell. From this lifewell, the lifedrinker draws the power needed to use their abilities. A lifedrinker gains lifewell points by bestowing negative levels and by dealing Constitution drain. Each negative level bestowed by a vampire&apos;s energy drain ability grants 2 lifewell points. Each point of Constitution drained grants 1 lifewell point. The lifewell of a lifedrinker can hold a maximum of 3 points per lifedrinker level. Lifewell points gained when the lifewell is already full are wasted.\n\nA lifedrinker with 0 lifewell points must succeed at a Will saving throw (DC 20) or go temporarily insane, attacking any living creature within sight until the lifewell has at least 1 point per lifedrinker level. A successful saving throw means that the lifedrinker need not make a saving throw against this temporary insanity until one week has passed and even then only if the lifewell has remained at 0 points throughout the week." compset="ClSpecial">
    <comment>How do I set a maximum charges of 3 per lifedrinker level.

How do I set a starting set of charges of 0.</comment>
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="500">field[hTotal].value = hero.child[cHelpLid].field[cTotalLev].value * 3</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidInvigo" name="Invigorate" description="A lifedrinker can spend 1 lifewell point to gain 1d6 temporary hit points. These hit points last 24 hours, and while they do not stack with those granted by other sources of temporary hit points, they do stack with more hit points gained from the invigorate ability, so a lifedrinker may spend multiple lifewell points to gain more temporary hit points. No more lifewell points may be spent on this ability in any given day than the lifedrinker has levels." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Can spend lifewell points to gain 1d6 temporary hit points.">
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidSBEmp" name="Spell Boost (Empower)" description="If a lifedrinker of 2nd level or higher casts spells, it may spend 4 lifewell points to empower a spell as if using the Empower Spell feat. The spell slot and level of the spell do not change." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Can spend 4 lifewell points to cast as spell as if {i}Empowered{/i}.">
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="2"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBoosSA" name="Boost Spell-Like Ability" description="{b}Benefit:{/b} The saving throw Difficulty Class (DC) of a boosted spell-like ability is increased by +2. Each of a creature&apos;s spell-like abilities can be boosted three times per day, though the feat does not allowthe creature to exceed its normal usage limit for any ability.\n\nThus, if a succubus chooses to boost its suggestion ability, it can use a boosted suggestion up to three times that day. Thereafter, it could use its suggestion ability again normally (since it can use suggestion at will), or it could boost another of its spell-like abilities, such as charmmonster.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} This feat can be taken multiple times. Each time it is taken, the creature can apply it to each of its spelllike abilities three additional times per day.\n{b}Source:{/b} Book of Vile Darkness" compset="Feat" summary="One of the creature&apos;s spell-like abilities is harder to resist than it otherwise would be.">
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidSBHeig" name="Spell Boost (Heighten)" description="If a lifedrinker of 3rd level or higher casts spells, it may spend a variable number of lifewell points to heighten a spell as if using the Heighten Spell feat. For every 2 lifewell points devoted to the spell boost, the spell&apos;s effective level is treated as one higher for purposes of save DC and other effects. For example, if a lifedrinker spends 4 lifewell points to boost a {i}fireball{/i} spell, the spell is treated as a 5th-level spell when calculating the Reflex save DC, and the boosted {i}fireball{/i} can penetrate a {i}minor globe of invulnerability{/i}, which a 3rd-level {i}fireball{/i} cannot. The spell slot and level of the spell do not change." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Can spend 2 per desired SL to cast a spell as if by the {i}Heighten{/i} spell feat.">
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="3"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidSABEmp" name="Special Attak Boost (Empower)" description="A 4th-level lifedrinker can spend 4 lifewell points to empower a special attack, increasing its variable, numeric effects by a factor of 1.5. The special attack is empowered for one use only. For example, a lifedrinker empowering its blood drain ability would drain 1d3 points of Constitution, multiplied by 1.5. A lifedrinker could also use this ability to summon more creatures using the children of the night ability it gains as a vampire. Some lifedrinkers might have other special abilities that they can use with this ability; a sea hag vampire lifedrinker, for example, could use this to empower her horrific appearance." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Can spend 4 lifewell points to empower special atks variable, numeric effects by X1.5.">
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="4"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidBloodS" name="Blood Servant" description="By spending 10 lifewell points, a 5th-level lifedrinker can call forth a {i}lesser planar ally{/i} (evil only), as per the spell of the same name.  The ally automatically serves the lifedrinker for 24 hours." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Can spend 10 lifewell points to summon a {i}lesser planar ally{/i} (evil) for 24 hours.">
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="5"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidBooDef" name="Boost Defenses" description="At 5th level, a lifedrinker can spend 8 lifewell points to add +2 to its natural armor bonus and turn resistance, add +10 to its cold resistance and electricity resistance, and increase its damage reduction to 20/+2. The effect lasts for 24 hours." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Spend 8 lifewell pts to gain +2 nat AC/Turn res, +10 cold/elec res, and incr. DR to 20/+2">
    <comment><![CDATA[Code from the Vampire Template:

      ~ Set up the amount of damage we resist
      #applyresist[xDamRsCold, 10]
      #applyresist[xDamRsElec, 10]

      ~ +4 Turn Resistance
      hero.child[xTurnRes].field[Value].value = maximum(hero.child[xTurnRes].field[Value].value, 4)

      ~ Fast Healing 5
      hero.child[xFastHeal].field[Value].value = maximum(hero.child[xFastHeal].field[Value].value, 5)


NOTE:
DR 20/+2 no longer exists in D&D 3.5, no equivalant form exsists so no upgrade can be coded.  Will consider adding some specials in the future.

Not working properly with the Augmented Vampire.]]></comment>
    <fieldval field="hName1" value="Active"/>
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="5"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="15000"><![CDATA[      if (field[hIsOn1].value <> 0) then

~ Add a +5 Untyped Bonus to our natural armor class
hero.child[ArmorClass].field[tACNatural].value = hero.child[ArmorClass].field[tACNatural].value + 2

hero.childfound[xTurnRes].field[Value].value = hero.childfound[xTurnRes].field[Value].value + 2

hero.childfound[xDamRsCold].field[Value].value = hero.childfound[xDamRsCold].field[Value].value + 10
hero.childfound[xDamRsElec].field[Value].value = hero.childfound[xDamRsElec].field[Value].value + 10
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidSBMaxi" name="Spell Boost (Maximize)" description="If a lifedrinker of 6th level or higher casts spells, it can spend 6 lifewell points to maximize a spell as if using the Maximize Spell feat. The spell slot and level of the spell do not change." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Can spend 6 lifewell points to cast as spell as if {i}Maximized{/i}.">
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="6"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidGrBlDr" name="Greater Blood Drain" description="At 7th level, a lifedrinker&apos;s blood drain ability now deals 1d6 points of Constitution drain." compset="ClSpecial" summary="At 7th level a a Lifedrinker&apos;s racial blood drain increases to 1d6 Constitution drain.">
    <comment>Cannot change the name of the Blood Drain ability for some reason.</comment>
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="7"/>
    <eval phase="Render"><![CDATA[~ hero.childfound[xBloodDra].field[xName].text "Greater Blood Drain"
hero.childfound[xBloodDra].field[xSumm].text = "Gain 5 Hp & deal d6 Con dam when pin foe, auto dam every rd maintain pin."

~ For Pathfinder Nosferatu Vampire:
hero.childfound[xPFNosBloo].field[xSumm].text = "Suck blood with a Grapple Check (1d6 CON + 1d4 WIS drain) to gain 5 HP."

~ For Augmented (Low-CR Vampires):
hero.childfound[xVamBlood].field[xSumm].text = "Suck blood with a Grapple Check (1d6 CON) to gain 5 HP."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidSABMax" name="Special Attak Boost (Empower)" description="A lifedrinker of 7th level or higher can spend 6 lifewell points to maximize all variable, numeric effects of a special attack. The special attack is maximized for one use only. A lifedrinker using this ability to maximize its greater blood drain ability, for example, would deal 6 points of Constitution drain. A lifedrinker could also use this ability to summon a maximum number of creatures using the children of the night ability it gains as a vampire. Some lifedrinkers might have other special abilities that they can boost in a similar fashion." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Can spend 6 lifewell points to maximize special atks variable, numeric effects.">
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="7"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpLid"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cLidSBQuic" name="Spell Boost (Quicken)" description="Spell Boost (Quicken) (Ex): If a lifedrinker of 8th level or higher casts spells, it can spend 8 lifewell points to quicken one of its spells, as if using the Quicken Spell feat. The spell slot and level of the spell do not change." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Can spend 8 lifewell pts cast a spell as if by the {i}Quicken{/i} spell feat.">
