  <thing id="cMorHunt1" name="Mortal Hunting +1" description="A mortal hunter gains a bonus against mortals due to its extensive study of them and train- ing in the proper combat techniques. The mortal hunter gains a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls against mortals and the same bonus on Bluff, Listen, Sense Motive, Spot, and Wilderness Lore checks when using these skills against mortals. The damage bonus applies to ranged weapons only against targets within 30 feet (the mortal hunter cannot strike with deadly accuracy beyond that range). The bonus does not apply to damage against creatures that are immune to critical hits. At 3rd, 6th, and 9th level, the mortal hunter&apos;s bonus associated with mortals goes up by +1. This bonus stacks with a ranger&apos;s favored enemy bonus." compset="ClSpecial" summary="+1 Bon, Atk/Dmg, Bluff, Listen, Sen Mot, Spot and Wildern. Lore (surv).">
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMor"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMorMSkin1" name="Mortal Skin (any humanoid)" description="By magically grafting bits of mortal flesh to its own body, a mortal hunter gains the ability at 1st level to transform (as the {i}polymorph self{/i} spell) into any humanoid mortal form.  At 5th level, a mortal hunter can polymorph into any mortal form except that of a dragon.  At 8th level, any mortal form can be adopted.  If the flesh used is from the exact individual being imitated, the duration is permanent.  If the flesh is from a being of the same type as the form adopted, the duration is 1 hour.  If the flesh is not the same type as the form adopted, the duration is 10 minutes.  In all cases, the mortal hunter can dismiss the ability as a standard action.  Otherwise, this ability works as the {i}polymorph self{/i} spell, and the mortal hunter can call upon it once per day." compset="ClSpecial" summary="1/day, use the skin of a slain mortal creature to take the form of a mortal.">
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpMor"/>
    </thing>
