6 Wrack DC 18
7 Wretched Blight (15d8 DC 23)</comment>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wand" name="Wand" abbrev="Wand"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="NoCharge"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="tmBVCorrup" name="Corrupted" description="CREATING A CORRUPTED CREATURE\n&#147;Corrupted&#148; is a template that can be added to any corporeal creature that is not an outsider (referred to hereafter as the base creature). Creatures that gain this template change their type to aberration. A corrupted creature uses all the base creature&#146;s statistics and special abilities except as noted here.\nAC: The flesh of corrupted creatures becomes tougher and more resilient. Add +4 to the natural armor bonus of the base creature if it is Large or smaller. If it is Huge or larger, add +8.\nDamage: The corrupted creature&#146;s claws lengthen, teeth multiply, and muscles harden. The damage die used when the creature deals damage with natural attacks increases by one die type, so that 1d6 becomes 1d8, 1d8 becomes 2d6, and so on, as if the creature were one size larger.\nSpecial Attacks: A corrupted creature retains all the special attacks of the base creature.\nSpecial Qualities: A corrupted creature retains all the special qualities of the base creature and also gains darkvision with a range of 60 feet plus acid immunity. It also gains the special qualities described below.\nDamage Reduction (Ex): Corrupted creatures gain damage reduction according to their Hit Dice.\n\n Hit       Damage\nDice   Reduction\n1&#150;3           &#151;\n4&#150;7        5/+1\n8&#150;11      5/+2\n12+       10/+3\n\nIf the base creature already has damage reduction, use the better value.\nDisruptive Attack (Su): The corrupt creature deals additional vile damage (see Chapter 2) when it touches uncorrupted, living, corporeal nonoutsiders. The amount of vile damage dealt is equal to half of the creature&#146;s Hit Dice (maximum 20 points of damage). For example, a 14-HD corrupted frost worm deals an additional 7 points of vile damage with its bite attack.\nEnhanced Power (Su): The save DCs of any and all of the corrupt creature&#146;s special attacks increase by +4.\nFast Healing (Ex): Each round, a corrupted creature heals damage equal to half of its Hit Dice (maximum of 10 points healed). If the base creature already has fast healing, use the better value.\nAbilities: Modify the base creature as follows: Str +4, Dex &#150;2, Con +4, Int +0,Wis &#150;2, Cha &#150;2.\nClimate/Terrain: Any land and underground.\nChallenge Rating: Up to 3 HD, same as base creature +1.\n4 HD to 7 HD, same as the base creature +2.\n8+ HD, same as the base creature +3.\nAlignment: Always evil." compset="Template" summary="Inherited Templated for creatures corrupted by evil." uniqueness="unique">
    <comment>Dont know how to handle Damage Reduction.</comment>
    <fieldval field="tmDEX" value="-2"/>
    <fieldval field="tmCON" value="+4"/>
    <fieldval field="tmWIS" value="-2"/>
    <fieldval field="tmCHA" value="-2"/>
    <fieldval field="tmSTR" value="+4"/>
    <usesource source="BoVD"/>
    <tag group="TemplHelp" tag="Inherited"/>
    <tag group="TemplHelp" tag="Acquired"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xFastHeal"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xImmAcid"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="rDarkVis2"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xDisrutAtk"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xEnhanPwr"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xDamRd1"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xDamRd2"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xDamRd3"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="Level" priority="101" index="2"><![CDATA[      var HD as number
      HD = herofield[tHitDice].value

      ~ Set up our damage reduction & Spell Resist Cold/Elec
      var value as number
      if (herofield[tHitDice].value <= 12) then
          #applydr[xDamRd3, 10]
      elseif (herofield[tHitDice].value <= 8) then
          #applydr[xDamRd2, 5]
      elseif (herofield[tHitDice].value <= 4) then
          #applydr[xDamRd1, 5]
        endif


      ~ We have Fast Healing half its HD (max 10)
      hero.child[xFastHeal].field[Value].value = maximum(10, HD/2)]]></eval>
    <eval phase="PreLevel"><![CDATA[      var result as number

      ~ bonus to natural armor based on size
      var bonus as number
      if (hero.tagis[Size.Small] <> 0) then
        bonus = 4
      elseif (hero.tagis[Size.Medium] <> 0) then
        bonus = 4
      elseif (hero.tagis[Size.Large] <> 0) then
        bonus = 4
      elseif (hero.tagis[Size.Huge] <> 0) then
        bonus = 8
      elseif (hero.tagis[Size.Gargantuan] <> 0) then
        bonus = 8
      elseif (hero.tagis[Size.Colossal] <> 0) then
        bonus = 8
      else
        bonus = 0
        endif
      hero.child[mNatural].field[Bonus].value = bonus

      ~ We have 60 foot Darkvision
      hero.child[rDarkVis2].field[Value].value = maximum(60, hero.child[rDarkVis2].field[Value].value)]]></eval>
    </thing>
